args: My first master was a tremendous fool. His greed,\ntemper, and lechery knew no bounds. His intellect\nand quality of character were nonexistent.

Why is it that these dolts manage to rise through
the ranks while the lowborn flounder in the dirt?
It always vexed me. That's why I swore I'd pull
myself up to the top using any means necessary.
I had to act, or nothing would change.\nI would use anyone or anything I needed\nto achieve my goals.
That's how I've lived my life,\never since I was a child...
You've devised a strategy to kill\nKing Leonidas?
I have indeed. You and I are the only\nones who know of our...twofold nature.\nWe are going to use that.
First, we will switch places. You will\nstand by at the northern border in order\nto create an alibi for yourself.

Meanwhile, I will kill the King and make
myself scarce. After that, all you have to
do is choose a culprit and become
everyone's hero.

With such a glorious exploit under your
belt, carrying out your revolution will
be child's play.
...Well?

(My scheme to kill the king was a bald-
faced lie. Now that he's waiting at the
checkpoint as planned, I'll strike him
down from behind!)
I don't recall advising you to stage\nan ambush as part of our plan.
Which plan was that, now?\nThe one to kill King Leonidas?
Or the one to kill me?
I did a bit of research into the\nconcept of other worlds myself.

If I were to die, then the existence of any
＂Harle＂ would become impossible within
this world. Now, what would happen after
that?
The realm would try to right itself,\nthereby removing you from it.
And you hoped to use that phenomenon\nas a means of returning to your world.\nDoes that about sum it up?
Brilliant work. I thought for certain my\nlie would be sufficient, but I suppose\nthere's no fooling myself.
You are me, after all. It's only natural\nthat I'd know exactly what you're thinking.
What a shame. I really thought we had a\nbeautiful partnership.
Faced with death, you lose your wits, I see.

I am of sound mind, I assure you.
I simply find your soldiers' loyalty
to you most amusing. They ought to
choose their leader more carefully..
Oh, you there. I'm about to die,\nso I'd like to give this to you.
Some kind of document?\n...Wh-what IS this?!
＂On Saving the Nation...＂ You want to\neliminate anyone too weak to be of use?
Oh, do be sure you read until the end.\nWhose signature is on there?
Harle... It can't be. You didn't write this,\ndid you, Prime Minister?
He did. It would seem that the great and\ntalented Harle of this world drafted this\nplan in hopes of saving Valkaheim.
He said there was no use wasting time\nand resources on the weak—no point in\ngiving them even a passing chance.
Hmph! What do I care if you show this\nto my soldiers here?

If you're interested in the specifics of
my plan, I will tell you all about it later.
Right now, you have a would-be assassin
to kill!
What are you waiting for?! KILL HIM!
We aren't going to listen to someone who\nwould stoop to such barbarism.
Excuse me?! ＂BARBARISM＂?\nIn a world brought to ruin, we have no\nchoice BUT to elevate the exceptional!
Ever hear of the food chain?\nYou're all benefiting from it!\nSo why does this bother you?!
But that doesn't mean that the strong\nshould rob the weak of the right to live!
Still your wicked tongue!\nThis is desertion—treason!
And so the pot admonishes the kettle.\nI understand now why you were at odds\nwith King Leonidas. Farewell.
Well, well. How the tables have turned.
You little...\nWhy did you have that with you?!
You are me, after all. It's only natural\nthat I'd know exactly what you're thinking.
I thought you might try to lure me into a\ntrap, so I brought it as a bit of insurance.
What lukewarm swordplay. Have you\nforgotten how to fight now that you're\nprime minister?
(We're one and the same. How can\nthe gulf between us be so wide?!)
(But even HE can't defend himself against\na sneak attack!)
What did I just say? I know\nEXACTLY what you're thinking.

I know that I would try to go after my
opponent's weak point. If you don't try
to fight fairly, I'll know exactly what
you're doing.
GRAAAGH! Nngh... Wait.\nLet's make a deal...
*cough* *wheeze* When I become\nruler, I'll share the position with you...
Not as my shadow, but as an equal.\nOur ideals are the same, aren't they?\nI'm offering you the deal of a lifetime...
Don't make me laugh.\nWe are nowhere near the same.

You became drunk with power. You forgot
what your ideals were. It makes me sick
to think you believe we're cut from the
same cloth.

My dream is to create a world where
everyone will be treated as equals,
regardless of the circumstances of
their birth or their social standing.

You've forgotten that. Otherwise, you
would never have thought to ＂trim the fat.＂
It's the exact kind of classism we swore
to eliminate.
There are fools and weaklings in this\nworld, to be sure. Though they may seem\nworthless at a glance, you can use them.
Have you forgotten that our path to\nknighthood was paved on the back of\nour nitwit master?

The real reason you're willing to cast
away the weak without a thought is
because you're afraid that someone
exceptional will rise up in the ranks.
You were afraid they might usurp your\nposition...the same way you did.

How funny it is that you fear your own
methodology. And yet, you rested on your
laurels, not even bothering to practice your
swordsmanship... How very sad for you.
You're no different from the weaklings\nyou sought to eliminate.
And like I said, even the weak have their\nuses—yours will be as my stepping stone.
Is this who I would become in the\nevent that my ideals are realized?
Oh... It's already started. Now, the\nquestion is whether I will disappear or\nreturn to my world. We're about to see.
I'll use anyone or anything I need to\nachieve my goals.
Even my own life!\nEven the very laws of nature!\nI will use it all!
